## How to Use Tokens as Tailwind Classes

| Token | Tailwind class examples |
|-------|------------------------|
| `--color-base` | `bg-base` |
| `--color-surface` | `bg-surface` |
| `--color-elevated` | `bg-elevated` |
| `--color-brand` | `bg-brand` `text-brand` `border-brand` `ring-brand` |
| `--color-brand-light` | `text-brand-light` `border-brand-light` |
| `--color-brand-dim` | `bg-brand-dim` |
| `--color-accent` | `text-accent` `bg-accent` |
| `--color-foreground` | `text-foreground` |
| `--color-muted` | `text-muted` |
| `--color-subtle` | `text-subtle` |
| `--color-success` | `text-success` `bg-success` |
| `--color-error` | `text-error` `bg-error` |
| `--radius-card` | `rounded-card` |
| `--radius-pill` | `rounded-pill` |
| `--shadow-card` | `shadow-card` |
| `--shadow-cta` | `shadow-cta` |

**Opacity modifier** вЂ” use Tailwind's `/` syntax for rgba borders:
```
border-brand/20   в†’  rgba(brand, 0.20)  в†ђ default card border
border-brand/45   в†’  rgba(brand, 0.45)  в†ђ hover / focus border
border-white/6    в†’  rgba(white, 0.06)  в†ђ subtle separator
bg-brand/15       в†’  rgba(brand, 0.15)  в†ђ tinted badge background
```

**Gradients and glows** вЂ” these still use `style={{ }}` since Tailwind cannot generate them:
```tsx
style={{ background: 'var(--gradient-cta)' }}
style={{ background: 'var(--gradient-hero)' }}
style={{ boxShadow: 'var(--shadow-brand)' }}
```

